  "rendered": {
    "title": "Multimodel support, smarter context handoff, and more resilient desktop packaging",
    "intro": "Today's nightly focused on a broad multimodel overhaul: hosted agents now route through AURA Proxy, model selection is wired end-to-end from the chat bar through dev-loop and task runs, and the model picker itself got a significant visual refresh. Alongside the product work, release infrastructure picked up automatic retry logic for transient Mac and Linux packaging failures.",
    "entries": [
      {
        "time_label": "12:15 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-18T07:15:02.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-18T07:15:02.000Z",
        "title": "AURA Proxy routing and end-to-end model wiring",
        "summary": "Hosted agents are now exclusively routed through AURA Proxy, and the actively selected model is propagated into dev-loop starts, task runs, and harness sessions.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Hosted Aura agents now use AURA Proxy as the sole credential and billing path — the agent editor UI was simplified to reflect this, removing the previous dual-choice between 'Managed by Aura' and an org integration.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "f365b8559c1ceae5ba98af87f8d4f9ee9450d821"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "The active model selection is now forwarded when starting or resuming a dev loop and when triggering manual task runs, so the model chosen in the UI is consistently used throughout execution.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "f4b5c6d127c2dc478f2e1b974b1ffdeb8d0f8d54",
              "8ec261b9d2b6caafeac4c17bf4a18f934125e222",
              "ea19f01383d670d1071e74d950ecfa1fdfccaea3",
              "9c6747900e77bc679566bd0769219141a81d223b"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Aura-managed proxy hints are now sent to harness sessions at runtime, and Fireworks-backed OSS model aliases are exposed for selection.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "76e0e4c75b51bd81fcf7e4174e7160a0e40aac60",
              "f093cef8cab08eca560fb77c613381118502eebd"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "time_label": "12:15 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-18T07:15:02.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-18T07:15:02.000Z",
        "title": "Model catalog refresh and chat picker redesign",
        "summary": "The model catalog was updated with current providers and Opus 4.6, the multimodel release candidate was narrowed, and the chat model picker received a significant layout and UX overhaul.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "The managed model catalog was refreshed to reflect current providers, and Opus 4.6 is now available in all Aura model pickers.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "f80524e58e66750b535cf755719cc0775bd794de",
              "287a3aad0a9001d6873ad2ab2c3c8f1538a43e4c"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "The chat model picker was redesigned with grouped sections, section labels, a scrollable dropdown (capped at 280px), and a 'show more' affordance — making it easier to navigate a growing model list.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "494aa6444163919b19fc5d0e674e7805959090af"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "When switching models mid-session, the agent now receives a snapshot of recent project specs and tasks as continuity context, preventing loss of project state across restarts or model changes.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "f2dc6b4064c670787ec2a20ed5032d0d70af649b"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Session event pagination was fixed to auto-paginate through full history when no explicit limit is set, preventing silent truncation at the previous 100-event server default.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "3a2dc62b4b36c5cd4de6baa2559d09ba812600a2"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "time_label": "2:10 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-18T09:10:15.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-18T09:10:15.000Z",
        "title": "Mac desktop packaging reliability fix",
        "summary": "Release Infrastructure: macOS DMG builds now automatically retry on transient hdiutil 'Resource busy' failures across nightly, stable, and validation workflows.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "All three desktop CI workflows (validate, nightly, stable) now detect and retry the intermittent macOS hdiutil 'Resource busy' error that was causing DMG packaging to fail spuriously on Mac.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "afa57d88238814b1502e0cf0861453de35eee3bb"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
